  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nYannick directed Manus to add 16 structured knowledge entries to Manus's native Knowledge Base instead of Notion. Manus generated structured entries (K1-K12 enabled, P1-P4 disabled) covering core operational protocols, identity, and project contexts. Manual copy-paste workflow established due to programmatic access limitations.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nConfigure Manus's knowledge base with core operational knowledge and project context to improve autonomous functioning and memory retention\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nGenerated 16 structured knowledge entries with titles and content formatted for manual addition to Manus Knowledge Base interface\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [structured_data] 16 Knowledge Base Entries — Core operational protocols (K1-K12) and project contexts (P1-P4) formatted for Manus Knowledge Base\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Use native Manus Knowledge Base instead of external Notion database\n- Enable K1-K12 operational entries, disable P1-P4 project entries initially\n- Manual copy-paste workflow due to programmatic access limitations\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Clear structure with enabled/disabled categorization\n- Formatted output ready for immediate use\nFailed / suboptimal:\n\n- Initial attempt to use Notion instead of native Knowledge Base\n- No programmatic access to Manus Knowledge Base interface\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Manus Knowledge Base requires manual entry via UI\n- Core operational knowledge can be structured into discrete entries\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- No programmatic API access to Manus Knowledge Base\n- Manual entry process required for 16 separate entries\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- How will these entries integrate with Manus's existing memory system?\n- Should project entries (P1-P4) be enabled later or kept as reference?\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Manual addition of all 16 entries via Manus Knowledge Base interface\n- Test knowledge integration in subsequent Manus sessions\n- Monitor how enabled entries affect Manus autonomous behavior\n---\nUID: f327wsFMTg4YUVXSRJzQ7n | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0149\n"
